1:46 PM Defendant Alan M Poblitz in court, in custody.  Attorney Peter M Wolff in court for Alan M Poblitz.  Prosecuting attorney Peter Michael Tempelis in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Victim A appeared by request in custody.
Case called for plea and sentencing. 
State places the offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty. 
Counts 1 & 3-11 are Dismissed and read in.

State and Defense make sentencing recommendations. 
Victim A makes statement to the court.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:

2  YEARS OF IMPRISONMENT (Credit: 111 Days)
18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
6 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
Consecutive to:  Any other sentence currently being served; 

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No contact with:  Victim A; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State-certified batterers intervention program;
*Anger Management;

RESTITUTION:  $0;
COSTS:  $268  
DOMESTIC VIOLENCE SURCHARGE: $100  
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250     
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
**To be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
The trial is removed from the calendar. 
Defendant may be returned to the appropriate facility forthwith.
